{
  "text": "Let G be a congruence subgroup of SL 2 (Z) and let X = X G be the corresponding modular curve which we shall suppose is defined over Q (sufficient conditions on G for this to hold are given in [9, Section 1.2]). Assume that X has genus g \u2265 2 and write J for the Jacobian of X. Let f 1 , . . . , f n be representatives of the Galois orbits of weight 2 cuspidal eigenforms for G (these may be computed via the modular symbols algorithm as in [CITATION_1] ). The theory of Eichler-Shimura attaches to each f i an abelian variety of GL 2 -type, which we shall denote by A i . Then",
  "citation_candidates": [
